<@U28TLDP0R> i implemented a new way to get decks from tappedout
python -c”import tappedout; tappedout.scan_commanders()”
basically the way it works is it does a specific tappedout search on each of the 648 commanders
it waits a minute between commander scans, thus taking about 11 hours in just sleeping (so probably 13-14 hours total)
i found that this search will get more decks
it might help with people complaining about not seeing their decks
ALSO, the other thing it does is it calls `make_commander` from nightly… so it updates the commander page as soon as it updates the commander’s decks
